# Environment Configuration Templates

## Backend Environment (.env)
Copy this to `backend/.env` and fill in your values:

```env
# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/SampleBlogs
MONGODB_TEST_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/SampleBlogsTest

# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# CORS
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

## Frontend Environment (.env.local)
Copy this to `frontend/.env.local` and fill in your values:

```env
# API Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

## Production Environment Variables

### For Backend Deployment (Heroku/Railway/DigitalOcean):
```env
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/SampleBlogs
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-domain.vercel.app
```

### For Frontend Deployment (Vercel/Netlify):
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend-domain.herokuapp.com/api
```

## MongoDB Atlas Setup
1. Create account at https://cloud.mongodb.com
2. Create a cluster
3. Create a database user
4. Get connection string
5. Replace `<password>` and `<dbname>` in the connection string

## Security Notes
- Never commit actual `.env` files to Git
- Use strong passwords for database connections
- Whitelist only necessary IP addresses in MongoDB Atlas
- Use environment variables in deployment platforms
